# Courses (N5 / N4 / N3)

All three JLPT courses share ONE engine. Adding a level = adding a data file; pages are generic.

## Lesson count is FLEXIBLE (IMPORTANT)
- Do NOT cap the number of lessons per level at a fixed number. Author as many lessons as needed to cover the FULL standard JLPT grammar syllabus for that level (N5/N4/N3).
- Lesson order may be (re)arranged for a sensible learning progression; renumber `id`/`number` (1..N) accordingly when reordering.
- Everything is data-driven: the `lessons` array length drives routes, nav, sitemap, and the quiz/listening/reading builders — so the count can grow freely with no code changes.

## Data (`src/constants/courses/`)
- `types.ts` – shared types: `Bilingual`, `VocabItem`, `GrammarExample`, `GrammarPoint`, `ReadingLine`, `ReadingChoice`, `ReadingQuestion`, `ReadingPassage`, `Lesson`, `Course`, `CourseLevel` (`'n5' | 'n4' | 'n3'`). Content is bilingual (`{ en, vi }`).
- `n5.ts`, `n4.ts`, `n3.ts` – each exports a `Course` (`n5Course` etc.) with `level`, `code`, `name`/`subtitle`/`intro`/`seoTitle`/`seoDescription` (all `Bilingual`, NOT translation keys) and a `lessons` array. Each lesson has `vocab`, `grammar`, and optional `reading` (a `ReadingPassage[]`; passages have `lines` + multiple-choice `questions` with bilingual `choices` and a `correctId`).
- `index.ts` – registry + helpers: `courses`, `courseList`, `COURSE_LEVELS`, `getCourse`, `getLesson`, `isCourseLevel`, path helpers (`coursePath`, `lessonPath`, `lessonExercisePath`, `lessonListeningPath`, `lessonReadingPath`), `lessonHasReading`, and `COURSE_SITEMAP_PATHS` (appended to `SITEMAP_PATHS` in `routes.ts`).

## Quizzes: NO romaji (IMPORTANT)
- Do NOT show romaji/phonetic transcription in the quiz surfaces (exercise / listening / reading). Quiz prompts, the listening reveal, and reading passages display Japanese (and meanings) only — no romaji helper line. Romaji stays on the lesson detail page only.

## Pages (`src/pages/course/`) — generic, take a `level: CourseLevel` prop
- `course-page.tsx` – course overview (lesson list, from course data).
- `lesson-page.tsx` – lesson detail (vocab + grammar with `SpeakButton`s) and CTAs to practice / listening / reading (reading button only if `lessonHasReading`).
- `exercise-page.tsx` + `course-quiz.ts` – mixed quiz (`ChoiceQuestion` + particle-cloze `InputQuestion`); the builder takes the whole `Course` for distractor pools.
- `listening-page.tsx` + `course-listening.ts` – audio quiz; plays `audioText` with `speakJapanese`.
- `reading-page.tsx` – reading comprehension: shows the passage (per-line `SpeakButton`, show/hide translation toggle) then steps through multiple-choice questions; reuses `ResultScreen`.
- `shared.tsx` – `LessonNotFound`, `ResultScreen` (both take `level`).

## Wiring
- Routes are registered ONCE in `src/app.tsx` by looping `COURSE_LEVELS`: `/:level`, `.../lesson/:lessonId`, `.../exercise`, `.../listening`, `.../reading`. `routes.ts` still declares `n5`/`n4`/`n3` index entries for SEO keys.
- `getSeoRouteKey` maps any `/n5|/n4|/n3` path to that level key; `page-meta.tsx` builds SEO from the course's `seoTitle`/`seoDescription` (via `isCourseLevel` + `getCourse`).
- Each course is a nav group generated from the registry in `src/constants/nav-items.ts` (`NavGroup.label?: Bilingual`); `app-layout.tsx` renders `group.label[locale]`.
- All shared course UI strings live under the `course.*` key namespace in `translations.ts` (en + vi). Per-level titles/intros come from course DATA, not translations.
